      "node_id": "PRRC_kwDOABII587DiVVg",
      "diff_hunk": "@@ -1374,6 +1356,60 @@ A few guidelines for modifying existing RPC interfaces:\n \n   - *Rationale*: Changes in RPC JSON structure can break downstream application compatibility. Implementation of `deprecatedrpc` provides a grace period for downstream applications to migrate. Release notes provide notification to downstream users.\n \n+## Feature deprecation and removal process\n+\n+Bitcoin Core uses a structured process for deprecating and removing features to give\n+downstream users and applications time to migrate.\n+\n+### General principles\n+\n+- The deprecation **grace period** is one major release. A feature deprecated in version N\n+  is expected to be removed in version N+1.\n+- Deprecation must be announced in the release notes of the version in which it is introduced.\n+- Removal must also be noted in the release notes of the version in which it occurs.\n+- Where possible, deprecated features should remain accessible via a re-enable flag during\n+  the grace period so downstream users are not immediately broken.\n+\n+### RPC methods and fields\n+\n+- To deprecate an entire RPC method or a backward-incompatible change to an existing method,\n+  gate the old behavior behind `-deprecatedrpc=<feature>`. During the grace period, users\n+  must explicitly opt-in to the deprecated behavior using this flag.\n+- The RPC help text must mention the deprecation, the planned removal version, and the\n+  `-deprecatedrpc=<feature>` flag that re-enables it during the grace period.\n+  See [example RPC help](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/94f0adcc/src/rpc/blockchain.cpp#L1316-L1323).\n+- Include a release note pointing users to the RPC help for details.\n+- In the removal release: remove the `-deprecatedrpc=` handling and the deprecated code path,\n+  and note the removal in release notes. See [#31278](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/31278)\n+  as a worked example.\n+\n+### Startup options\n+\n+- To deprecate a startup option, emit a warning via `LogWarning` or `InitWarning` when the\n+  option is used, so users are notified at startup.\n+- Update the option's help text to indicate it is deprecated and will be removed in the next\n+  major release.\n+- Include a release note.\n+- In the removal release: remove the option and its handling, and note the removal in release\n+  notes.\n+\n+### REST interface\n+\n+- Deprecated REST endpoints or behaviors should be documented in `doc/REST-interface.md`\n+  with the version they were deprecated and the planned removal version.\n+- Include a release note.\n+\n+### ZMQ\n+\n+- Deprecated ZMQ topics or behaviors should be documented in `doc/zmq.md` with the version\n+  they were deprecated and the planned removal version.\n+- Include a release note.\n+\n+### Wallet settings\n+\n+- Wallet settings exposed as RPC methods follow the [RPC deprecation process](#rpc-methods-and-fields).\n+- Wallet settings exposed as startup options follow the [startup option process](#startup-options).",
